  "texts": [
    "In the first step of Tokenization, algorithms segment the text data into words and phrases, and these tokens become the input for the NLP task (Webster & Kit, 1992).",
    "The tokenizer converts the string of technical text into individual tokens, but the short hand of L/E, used to denote the leading edge is not tokenized correctly.",
    "It is split up into separate tokens for each character instead.",
    "We then use the individual tokens from tokenization as the input for the next step of stop word removal.",
    "Stop words are considered to be unimportant words that provide little information (Manning & Schutze, 1999)."
  ],
